-- Clariant Said to Sell 500 Million Euros of Five-Year Bonds
-- B y   H a n n a h   B e n j a m i n
-- 2012-01-17T08:41:34Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-17/clariant-said-to-sell-500-million-euros-of-five-year-bonds.html
Clariant AG (CLN)  plans to sell 500
million euros of five-year bonds, according to a banker involved
in the transaction.  The bonds may be priced to yield 425 to 437.5 basis points
more than the benchmark mid-swap rate, the banker said. BNP
Paribas SA, Citigroup Inc. and  UniCredit SpA (UCG)  are managing the
deal.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Hannah Benjamin in London at 
 hbenjamin1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Ben Martin at 
 bmartin38@bloomberg.net  